---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
const schema = [
  {
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Best Wireless Gaming Mice",
    "description": "Best wireless gaming mice \u2014 latency, battery, weight comparison.",
    "@context": "https://schema.org"
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do wireless mice have more input lag?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No, modern 2.4GHz wireless technologies from top brands have input latency equal to or sometimes even better than standard wired mice."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long do wireless gaming mice batteries last?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Depending on usage, RGB settings, and polling rate, modern batteries can last anywhere from 40 to 150 hours on a single charge."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Are wireless gaming mice heavier?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "While they contain batteries, significant engineering advancements mean top wireless mice are often just as light as wired options, frequently dropping below 60g."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];
---
<SiteLayout site="leeroyjenkins" title="Best Wireless Gaming Mice" description="Best wireless gaming mice — latency, battery, weight comparison." canonical="https://leeroyjenkins.quest/best-wireless-gaming-mouse" schema={schema}>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero"><h1>Best Wireless Gaming Mice</h1><p>Best wireless gaming mice — latency, battery, weight comparison.</p></div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>Top Wireless Mice</h2>
      <p>Wireless technology is the current standard for high-end gaming mice. The freedom from cable drag significantly improves aiming consistency.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Logitech G Pro X Superlight 2:</strong> {null}</li>
        <li><strong>Razer DeathAdder V3 Pro:</strong> {null}</li>
        <li><strong>Ninjutso Sora:</strong> {null}</li>
        <li><strong>Lamzu Atlantis:</strong> {null}</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>Key Features of Wireless Mice</h2>
      <h3>Latency and Connection</h3>
      <p>Never use Bluetooth for gaming. Top-tier wireless mice use dedicated 2.4GHz USB dongles to achieve 1ms (or even 0.125ms at 8000Hz polling) response times. This matches and sometimes exceeds the performance of wired connections.</p>

      <h3>Battery Life vs. Weight</h3>
      <p>The primary engineering challenge is balancing battery capacity with total weight. To keep weights low, companies use smaller batteries, meaning you may need to charge them more frequently. Disabling RGB lighting is the fastest way to extend battery life.</p>

      <h3>4K and 8K Polling Rates</h3>
      <p>Newer wireless models offer 4000Hz or 8000Hz polling rates, meaning the mouse reports its position up to 8000 times per second instead of the standard 1000. While this reduces latency marginally, it heavily impacts battery life.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <dl>
        <dt>Do wireless mice have more input lag?</dt>
        <dd>No, modern 2.4GHz wireless technologies from top brands have input latency equal to or sometimes even better than standard wired mice.</dd>

        <dt>How long do wireless gaming mice batteries last?</dt>
        <dd>Depending on usage, RGB settings, and polling rate, modern batteries can last anywhere from 40 to 150 hours on a single charge.</dd>

        <dt>Are wireless gaming mice heavier?</dt>
        <dd>While they contain batteries, significant engineering advancements mean top wireless mice are often just as light as wired options, frequently dropping below 60g.</dd>
      </dl>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>Related Guides</h2>
      <div class="cluster-links">
        <div class="cluster-link-card"><a href="/best-gaming-mice-2026">Best Gaming Mice 2026</a> (Pillar)</div>
        <div class="cluster-link-card"><a href="/best-fps-mouse">Best FPS Mice</a></div>
        <div class="cluster-link-card"><a href="/mouse-switch-guide">Switch Guide</a></div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
  <script is:inline>

  </script>
  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .hero p { color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    .card h2 { margin-top: 0; color: var(--text-primary); }
    .card h3 { color: var(--text-primary); }
    th, td { padding: 0.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color); text-align: left; }
    table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; }
    ul, ol { padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-top: 1rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold; }
    a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
    dl { margin-top: 1rem; }
    dt { font-weight: bold; margin-top: 1rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
    dd { margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-top: 0.5rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .cluster-links { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; margin-top: 1rem; }
    .cluster-link-card { background: var(--bg-color); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; text-align: center; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
